    "Mastitis": {
      "text": "No need to routinely interrupt breastfeeding with puerperal mastitis.\nFor mild symptoms <24 hours, supportive care may be sufficient\n[7]\nEffective milk removal (frequent breast feeding - use pumping to augment milk removal)\nAnalgesia (NSAIDs)\nTreatment directed at\nS. aureus\nand\nStrep\nand\nE. coli\nUncomplicated mastitis â†’ 10 days of antibiotics (regardless of\nMRSA\nsuspicion)\n[8]\nDicloxacillin\n500mg PO q6hrs, considered first line if breastfeeding given safety for infant\nOR\nCephalexin\n500mg PO q6hrs\nOR\nAdd\nTMP/SMX\n2DS tabs PO q12hrs if suspect\nMRSA\nClindamycin\n450mg PO q8hrs (also provides MRSA coverage)\nOR\nAmoxicillin/Clavulanate\n875mg PO q12hrs\nOR\nAzithromycin\n500mg PO x1 on day 1, then 250mg PO daily for days 2-5",
